## ⚙️ 2. C&C STRUCTURES (RUNTIME VIEW)

### 🧩 Intuition
Not “who depends on who”  
But **“who talks to who while running”**

### 📘 Components vs Connectors

**Components** (units that execute at runtime)  
Examples in Keras:
- Model
- Layer
- Optimizer
- Loss

**Connectors** (interactions between components)  
Examples:
- Function calls
- Tensor flow
- Gradient updates

### 🔄 Runtime Interactions

**🧩 Intuition**  
Think of a pipeline:

```
Input → Process → Output
```

**🔥 Keras Training Flow**

```
Input → Forward → Loss → Backward → Update
```

**🧱 C&C Diagram**

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Data
    participant Model
    participant Layer
    participant Ops
    participant Backend
    participant Optimizer

    Data->>Model: input x
    Model->>Layer: forward
    Layer->>Ops: compute
    Ops->>Backend: execute
    Backend-->>Ops: result
    Ops-->>Layer: tensor
    Layer-->>Model: output
    Model->>Model: compute loss
    Model->>Optimizer: update weights
```

### 💡 Key Insight
Connectors define:
- Data flow
- Control flow
- Execution order

